casebody.data:
LOUISVILLE PROVISION CO. et al. v. Seldon R. GLENN, Collector, etc., et al. No. 7680. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit June 28, 1937. Woodward, Dawson & Hobson and Steinfeld & Steinfeld, all of Louisville, Ky., for appellants. Bunk Gardner, of Louisville, Ky., for appellees.

Before HICKS and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

HICKS, Circuit Judge.

On motion of appellants, it is ordered that the appeal herein (18 F.Supp. 423) be and the same is dismissed, without prejudice at the cost of appellants.
